					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Erudite Magician</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:kwiksak@fiberia.com">Auir Skyphire</a> | 
		            11/27/1999 12:43:36 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">This is the guide for the 1st time player of the Erudite magican. In my opinion the best magican. Other guides, in my opinion seem to want to rush you off to a new zon ASAP, personally I dont like playing that way. I find hanging around a particular zone makes you well known and makes a big difference when the magicain needs to group at high levels<BR>
<BR>
1-4 Hunt in your native newbie zone. Other gudes tell you to go to Qeynos. Personally I stayed in Erudin becasue I got better deals on buying and selling, and ultimately I met some of my long lasting freinds there. Hunt your general, snakes, decaying skelletons etc.. especially kobold runts, they are easy money.<BR>
<BR>
5-6 Go accross the bridge and hunt in the kobold camps. I found that a partner is very usefull on occasion here, skeletons had the worst timing and can cause problems. <BR>
 --sidenote for lvl 6 I also got a group and camped that necro by the docks and the troll and did some quests involving them.<BR>
<BR>
6-7 I went to Kerra isle here, it was really tough. I had a hard time gathering any types of group to hunt here. But luckily the freinds I had met here had also stayed in the Erudin area. I also found that at this stage my pets were worthless against the Kerrans. At this level you might want to head over to Black Burrow.<BR>
<BR>
8-17 Hunt in Black Burrow. I belive I hunted on the top floor of Black Burrow untill I reached level 10. I would go around picking off gnolls at their spawns, and picking off choice gnolls off the inevidabel trains. (LEARN TO HATE THEM) 10-14 I hunted various things and I learned how to camp like a pro. The &quot;commander room&quot; was a great spot for camping and soloing. 15-17 Get a group together and camp the &quot;green room&quot;. I did this for a seemingly long time, and made some more freinds here. While in here with a full group I didnt need to have a pet, that thing would cause more problems than for what it was worth. When I was unable to get a group I would head over to Everfrost and solo mamoth calfs(very trickey).<BR>
<BR>
18-21 I hunted in oasis. This is THE PLACE for any class/race in this level range. This is also a good place because it is near the Ocean of Tears, where you can buy the level 16 and 20 pet spells.<BR>
Near level 20-21 hunt the crocs that say deepwater. During peak hours this plcae goes bad for crocs, so i would head over to the dervish camp, orc camp, or the &quot;orc highway&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
Right now im level 22 and Im sort of lost as where my next long term hunting spot will be, I have gone to Everfrost to hunt momma mamoths, Runneye (ugh the trains the trains, I really dont recomend) and Lake rathere/ south karana. I believe I will hang around there untill level 24 hunting elephants centaurs, and Aviaks. From there I think Najina (spelling) is a good spot.<BR>
<BR>
easy quest for a fairly nice weapon, I had mine till level 20, is the one offered in the Wizards Guild in Erudin. They give you the servants staff +5 mana (1hb) Much better than Ruined totem staff (2hb), beacasue somewhere in your mid teens you will get your hands<BR>
on a skull of jhen`ra. <BR>
<BR>
At level 16 you get the spell summon throwing daggars, BUY IT!!! Learn to throw really good. I think the cap is 75 for us. Evenually you wont be holding any  weapons, and those daggars deal  up to 6 dammage and are VERY helpfull. Against bigger foes you have the potential of dealing 120 dammage with 20 daggars. :)<BR>
<BR>
Fire shields/flame shields etc.. allways throw them on your pet or party members = more dammage. <BR>
<BR>
And finnaly dont use fire or air pets because they just plain bite.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Auir Skyphire<BR>
Level 22 Magician<BR>
&lt;The Peoples Front of Norrath&gt;<BR>
The Tribunal server
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
